templateAssets.content: Competency (successfully completing the third college semester or fifth college quarter) is required in one foreign language to fulfill graduation requirements for this major.

Due to high demand, admission to SDSU is highly competitive. General admission information is available at:http://arweb.sdsu.edu/es/admissions/transfers/index.html For additional information regarding admission to specific majors, please visit the SDSU Transfer Admission Planner (TAP) site:https://sunspot.sdsu.edu/pubred/!tap.disp

templateAssets.content:
1. Complete with a minimum GPA of 2.50 and a grade of C (2.0) or better: RWS 100, RWS 200; COMM 103; ECL 220 or C LT 270A or C LT 270B; JMS 200; HUM 140; LING 101; six units from ENGL 250A and ENGL 250B or ENGL 260A and ENGL 260B; ECL 280. These courses cannot be taken for credit/no credit (Cr/NC);
  2. Have a cumulative GPA of 2.40 or better.
